<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='486000' id='t-486000'>no one can learn.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='488000' id='t-488000'>And what happens when the teacher tries to assert order?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='492000' id='t-492000'>They're threatened with a legal claim.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='494000' id='t-494000'>We also surveyed that. Seventy-eight percent of the middle and high school teachers</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='497000' id='t-497000'>in America have been threatened by their students</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='500000' id='t-500000'>with violating their rights, with lawsuits</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='502000' id='t-502000'>by their students. They are threatening, their students.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='505000' id='t-505000'>It's not that they usually sue,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='507000' id='t-507000'>it's not that they would win, but it's an</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='510000' id='t-510000'>indication of the corrosion of authority.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
